cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) because it proposes a desynchronization algorithm for wireless sensor networks. It may also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) because it deals with coordinating access to a shared resource. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) because it uses dynamical systems to analyze stability. It may also be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) because it deals with resource utilization and channel fairness. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) because it involves coordinating the behavior of multiple nodes in a network.
